channel.title: The weirdest thing
channel.description:
This doesn't really make sense to me, but I'll see if someone else can explain this for me. Basically, I used to run a server about 2 years ago, and lately decided to start up again for fun. I've forgotten like everything haha and for some reason I can't get my shit to work. I have Java, my host on the No-ip website set up, I correctly portforwarded, and have the environmental variables set up. But for some reason I can't log into my server. I compile and run the run.bat (there's no errors and the run.bat says "Server online!' just like it should, but then I try to log in from the Silab webclient and it just says "Error connecting to server".
Maybe things are different now and there's some other step I need to do to make the connection between the webclient and my server (Although I DID enter in my correct IP that I set up on the No-ip website), but I'm really at a loss here.
